<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1951-12-28T19:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1951-12-28T19:00:00-05:00" n="564" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d564">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">320/12–2351: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                                    (<persName type="to"><hi rend="italic">Austin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi>
                                </seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1951-12-28T19:00:00-05:00">December 28, 1951—7:01 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_Gadel2">Gadel</gloss> 562. Re Indians in South
                                Africa <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss>s 754 and 800. <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes five power draft Res as
                                unlikely achieve desired end as last year’s Res and previous
                                efforts. Passage wld only exacerbate feelings, solve nothing and
                                keep problem coming back in <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> every
                                year.</p>
                            <p>While <gloss target="#t_Dept1">Dept</gloss> believes chance of
                                settlement this case thru <gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> action
                                remote, sees no harm in attempting a fresh approach such as <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> idea of neutral individual to
                                bring parties together. We believe however <pb facs="0883" n="861" xml:id="pg_861"/>
                                <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> has gone as far as it can or
                                shld at this time by planting seed. If it germinates in minds of
                                sponsors you may help in pruning, but if it needs cultivating UK
                                shld be head gardener in commonwealth garden.</p>
                            <p>
                                <gloss target="#t_USDel1">USDel</gloss> shld approach <gloss target="#t_UKDel1">UKDel</gloss> on this basis to encourage UK
                                play lead in seeking solution.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Acheson</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>